    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="516"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <head>516. Telegram 1586 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d516fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/3–356. Official Use
                        Only; Priority. Repeated for information Priority to Prague for the
                        Ambassador as telegram 26.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-03-03"
                            >March 3, 1956, 3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d516-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d516-1"/>
                <p>1586. From Osborn. My telegram sent Department 1585 repeated information Prague
                    26.</p>
                <p>Reporters say Chinese Communist Consulate General has announced postponement
                    release, no indication until then.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Note: FE Duty Officer notified 3/3/1:15 p.m. LWH</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
